        <div class="faq-a">The main current global conflicts in 2025 include the Russia-Ukraine war, the Israel-Gaza conflict, Taiwan Strait tensions, the Sudan civil war, Myanmar's ongoing civil conflict, Houthi Red Sea attacks, and Sahel instability (Mali, Niger, Burkina Faso). Orreryx tracks all of these and dozens more in real time.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is war monitoring and how does Orreryx do it?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">War monitoring is the systematic real-time tracking of armed conflicts and military developments worldwide. Orreryx pulls from GDELT, 45 RSS news feeds, and wire services, then categorizes, geo-tags and ranks each event by severity. Events appear on the live map within minutes of being reported.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How does geopolitical news affect markets in 2025?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Geopolitical events move markets in direct, predictable ways: wars drive defence stocks (LMT, RTX, NOC) and oil prices up; sanctions disrupt supply chains and currencies; elections shift emerging market equities. Orreryx maps this cause-and-effect live so you can act before the market fully prices in the news.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is Orreryx free?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Orreryx offers a 3-day free trial with no credit card required. You get full access to the live geopolitics news feed, war monitoring dashboard, 3D world map, AI briefings and stock screener. Plans start at $0.99/month after trial.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
